body:
During the first 6 months of YouSwap's operations, it became noticeable that the platform's mechanism for destroyed 100% of handling fees caused operational issues as the market maker was unable to generate sufficient revenue, resulting in insufficient liquidity on the trading platform and thus not conducive to the ecological development of the platform;


In view of this, with the upcoming launch of the YouSwap v2.0 version, there will be adjustment to the current fee distribution model to sustain and maintain the development of YouSwap. The adjustment plan is as follows:


A transaction fee of 0.3% is charged for exchange, of which 0.25% will be used for market-making mining and allocated to SLP (allowing for the AMM mechanism to be deployed across the network), and 0.05% to be used used for repurchase and destruction.
